title: Capusa senilis
text:
Capusa senilis, the black-banded wedge-moth, is a <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Geometridae">Geometridae</a>. The species was <a href="Species%20description">first described</a> by <a href="Francis%20Walker%20%28entomologist%29">Francis Walker</a> in 1857. It is found in the south-eastern quarter of <a href="Australia">Australia</a>.
The larvae feed on <a href="Fabaceae">Fabaceae</a>, <a href="Myrtaceae">Myrtaceae</a> and <a href="Pinaceae">Pinaceae</a> species.
